wikipedia_page.main: Kelsi Melanie Fairbrother-Svane (born 5 August 1989 in Hillingdon) is a British handball player. She plays for the British national team and competed at the 2012 Summer Olympics in London. She married Kris Svane on 18 July 2013 and now uses Kelsi Fairbrother-Svane as her married name. She played for the club Team Esbjerg until January 2014, when she announced her immediate move to Thuringer HC.

response: Sarah Hargreaves (born 17 May 1989, Fårevejle, Sjaelland) is a British handball goalkeeper. She has played for the British national team, qualifying thanks to her British father, and competed at the 2012 Summer Olympics in London. At the time of her participation in the 2012 Olympics, her club is Slagelse FH. She was one of only two players in the squad, along with Kelsi Fairbrother, to remain with her club team instead of joining the British programme in Crystal Palace.
